text:
Very bad attitude from the stall owner. Ordered a packet of duck rice to go and wanted to pay but the QR code wasn't working. (I tried using 2 different phones). Asked nicely if there is any other QR code to scan, they are so defensive and said that's the only one and other people can scan. Others paid $300+ and blamed on my phone. Asked me to change hp.

Won't revisit!

Scammers, asked for $7 portion, gave me $5 portion. Not the way to do business, unethical, stupid aunty and uncle. Still can lie through their teeth and say "alr add meat liao" . Is this what you call "add meat"?

Came here after a recommendation by a friend. After trying their braised duck noodles, I wasn't really impressed. Noodles were well cooked. Duck meat was a bit hard and tough. Braised egg was hard as well. Their soup had a mild herbal taste and was a bit too peppery. I felt that they could definitely do better than this. Just my personal opinion.

Good Kuay Chap with braised duck at an old time joint. Enjoyable meal. This is one of 5 outlets spread across Bishan, Joo Chiat, Ang Mo Kio, Adam Road, and Lavender. Their main store is at Kim San Leng Food Court, Bishan.

I boycotting this shop, because their duck rice stall don't provide soup!

Go and eat their duck rice if u ok without soup! Not sure the staff lazy or really don't provide soup at Empress mall?

You guys are not the only one in Singapore lei!

How come your staff(a lady) at empress mall told me they don't provide soup for their happy duck rice, I'm very unhappy now!

Not sure the staff lazy or really don't provide soup at Empress mall?
